text: (ALL) Yeah!
(Man A) It’s Christmas! It’s my favorite time of the year!
(Woman) Christmas! Christmas!
(Man B) Christmas!
(Woman) Hey, what’s with the long face? What’s wrong?
(Man A) Come on! It’s a party!
(Man B) What’s the matter?
(Man A) Stop being such a wet blanket.
(Woman) Come on, you. Don’t be a drag.
(Man A) That’s right! We’ve got roasted chicken and cake all ready and waiting.
(Woman) I bought the cake. I got it for you. Doesn’t it look good?
(Man A) Looks good.
(Man B) Yes.
(Woman) I know.
(Man A) Let’s dig in!
(Woman) Wait wait wait..you’re getting ahead of yourself here.
(Man A) How did you know?
(Woman) It's obvious. That’s not good. We’ll share it equally.
(Man A) I’m sorry.
(Man B) Listen, listen…I have something to say. Will you listen to me?
(Woman) What is it?
(Man A) Tell me.
(Man B) Hear me out.
(Man A) What is it?
(Man B) This cake’s fine but have a look at this salad!
I made this salad.
All the vegetables in this salad are completely natural.
Do you know what it means by all natural?
Not organic, but natural, right?
(Woman) Oh, no. here we go!
(Man A) Every time the subject of vegetables comes up he won’t stop talking about it! He’s a real vegetable freak!
(Man B) Speaking of organic farming
it is the cultivation using organic fertilizers such as animal excrement and plant waste.
On the other hand, natural farming is the cultivation
without any use of pesticides and fertilizers.
All natural vegetables are not widely available because they require great care
but they are delectable and bring out the original taste of vegetables.
…are you listening to me?
(Man A) I haven’t been listen at all.
(Man B) You don't listen at all, do you?
(Woman) You get carried away.
(Man B) Why don’t you listen to me?
(Man A) All your talk about vegetables is boring!
(Woman) Oh!
(Man AB) Oh my!
(Woman) What the…..!
That dog scared the crap out of me!
You’re the one who brought it, didn’t you?
(Man A) Ha-ha-ha! It scared you to death.
(Woman) Hey, are you listening?
(Man B) This dog has special powers.
(Man A) A super natural dog?
(Woman) Hmm, is that so?
(Man B) This dog protects people from bad things. It’s a guardian against evil.
It’s a Christmas present for all of us.
(Woman) You brought it?
(Man B) Uh-huh.
(Man A) Bringing a super natural lucky dog for Christmas...
(Woman) What does this mean?
(Man B) I don’t know what it is…but having a party in this room just feels wrong?
(Man A) What are you talking about?
(Man B) I’ve got a bad feeling from this room.
(Woman) What kind of feeling?
(Man B) Can’t you feel it?
There’s a strange aura about this room.
(Man A) I can’t really explain it.
(Man B) When you put it like that, I do feel a sense of being watched.
Things move around by themselves.
(Woman) Hey, come on, let’s change the subject. Let’s talk about something else.
(Man B) Don’t you feel it?
This room is alive with something.
(Woman) Come on, hey, it’s Christmas. Let’s put a sock in it.
(Man A) You’re scared, aren’t you. Huh?
(Woman) ...um. I’m not scared. I don’t scare easily.
Come on, don’t look at me like that.
(Man A) Yeah, that’s it. You’re scared.
(Woman) No, that’s not it. It’s not that I’m scared.
I can’t quite put my finger on it.
(ALL) Oh Gosh!
(Woman) Sorry, sorry. It was my alarm.
(Man A) Ah! Come one, cut it out. Are you kidding me? Your alarm?
(Man B) Stop it.
(ALL) OMG!
(Man A) What the….? Did something drop?
(Man A) What is this?
(Man B) I’m feeling queasy.
(Woman) If this is some kind of joke, cut it out!
(Man A) Nobody is doing anything!
(Woman) What?
(Woman) What the! I definitely don’t like this room!
(Man B) I’m scared! I’m scared!
(Man A) What is going on?
(Woman) I quit!
(Man A) Come on, cut it out!
